    <text>
        <body>
            <pb facs="MSVIII77r"/>
            <div type="witness" subtype="poem" rhyme="aabbccddefefghghghiijjkkllccaammnn" met="-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|-+|">
               <head type="title"><handShift new="#HANDJR1833-34" script="cursive" medium="ink"/>Continuation of Vintage</head>
                <lg type="stanza">
                    <l>It chanced, that on that vintage time, in order set, were <add place="above"><space quantity="51" unit="chars"/>seen</add></l>
                    <l>Two casks of sparkling with<!--?--> champagne, a cask of port between</l>
                    <l>Outflanked were they by sherry butts, some claret standing <add place="above"><space quantity="53" unit="chars"/>near</add></l>
                    <l>And who shall blame safe <!--illeglible word--> hock for bringing up the rear</l>
                    <l>I scarcely know <del rend="strikethrough">how</del> now how it was, but certes the Champagne</l>
                    <l>Was frisky, hot, resembling not the steady <!--illegible word--> from <placeName corresp="SPAIN">Spain</placeName>&#x2014;</l>
                    <l>He quarrelled with his company &#x0026; nearly burst his butt</l>
                    <l>And straight attacked the good old port, when cellar doors were <add place="above"><space quantity="56" unit="chars"/>shut</add></l>
                    <l><!--Random dot before line-->Thou crusty old rascal <add place="above"><space quantity="23" unit="chars"/>&#x201C;</add>&#x2014; <!--" is placed above the dash-->the Champagne said</l>
                    <l>(And foamed &#x0026; fizzed forth indignation</l>
                    <l>How dar&#x02BC;st thou come near with thy nose so red</l>
                    <l><!--illegible word--> Or approximate thy situation&#x2014;</l>
                    <l>To mine you dull body, to mine I say</l>
                    <l>Be off &#x2014; or Ill bang in your bung</l>
                    <l>We&#x02BC;ll see who&#x02BC;s most spirit&#x2014; Port kept him at bay</l>
                    <pb facs="MSVIII77v"/>
                    <l>Quoth he&#x2014;&#x201C;You&#x02BC;re not wanting in tongue.</l>
                    <l>I&#x02BC;m a quiet old gentleman, not much to say</l>
                    <l>But I wont take affront, so have done.</l>
                    <l>And port looked to the sherry, and tipped him the wink<!--Best logical guess due to scratch-out--></l>
                    <l>And I wish you had seen how the champagne grew pink</l>
                    <l>Almost scarlet with rage, you&#x02BC;d have thought it demented</l>
                    <l>The sputtered and stuttered and fizzed &#x0026; fermented</l>
                    <l>Nor long within those wooden walls had remained</l>
                    <l>The casks yielding timbers they creaked &#x0026; complained</l>
                    <l>Then streams of rich wine through the cellar had ran</l>
                    <l>But with calmness, composing the sherry began<!--Em-dash?--></l>
                    <l>Thou wert quarrelsome always, thou heady champagne</l>
                    <l>We know thee of old <space quantity="4" unit="chars"/> Must I tell thee again</l>
                    <l>We have pardoned thy faults, for we know &#x0026; have seen</l>
                    <l>Thou wert pressed from the grape when twas acid &#x0026; green</l>
                    <l>But dost think that the wines will have thee for their lord,</l>
                    <l>They rather will give you presumptions reward</l>
                    <l>Discard from their presence a subject so bold</l>
                    <l>So his pride be abased, and his passion controlled</l>
                </lg>
